# good

Renders approved engineering patterns. The "do not substitute alternatives, even equivalent-seeming ones" clause is essential — it closes the gap between what the model thinks is equivalent and what the codebase has explicitly adopted.

# entity Input

- directive: 'good'
- name: undefined — good is always anonymous
- body: required patterns, proven approaches, and style mandates

# entity Output

```markdown
## [ENFORCED CODING DESIGN PATTERNS]

Apply every pattern and practice listed below in all generated code without exception. These are validated, required standards for this codebase — do not substitute alternatives, even equivalent-seeming ones:

{{body}}
```

# rule

- good blocks carry no name. A name field on a good block is a PARSE_ERROR.
- Multiple good blocks across cascade levels are merged in cascade order and rendered as one section.
